      "writtenOn": "2018-03-27T16:03:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The default Behavior above is to clear the entire struct to 0, and I think SW should be allowed by default?\n\nIn reality I would prefer to take out that entire field, but clip mask rendering requires it. How would you feel about first modifying the clipping code to always use the software path when creating an alpha mask? With ccpr and analytic FPs, that will be uncommon, and I think for generating a single clip mask, the software path will almost always be faster anyway.\n\nIf we take out the GPU path from clip masks, we don\u0027t need the fAllowSoftwareRenderer field anymore.\n\nAlternatively we could just allow the software renderer in the GPU clip mask path and not need this field either.",
      "parentUuid": "e9ebf968_6a18894f",
